         <abstract id="aspace_9abf93da70f11eed3f187482e3464ad5">The collection consists of plates, scrapbooks, and dress pattern catalogs, depicting European and American fashion, costume, and national dress primarily from the 18th and 19th centuries.</abstract>
         <langmaterial id="aspace_10186f00df4d18534098817bc504fc01">
            <language>In English, French, and German.

</language>
         </langmaterial>
    
      </did>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_624c2738e2940c07f01ac27a9daf6db7">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The collection consists of plates collected by the Drama Library and the Arts of the Book Collection over many years. Scrapbooks were the gift of Mrs. Bertram W. Martus to the Drama Library, 1960.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_a907df62fe1413ecc54d493e1e5b6829">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_b1481875c3aadc2108f88ee946962c55">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_0e74f2c9ee9165f0e6d1b7f82aba804e">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Fashion and Costume Plate Collection, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_d7f9ee616f659e585d0db08cce0413fc">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection consists of fashion plates from British, American, and French publications dating from the 18th through 19th centuries, including <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>Gallery of Fashion</part>
            </title> and <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>Modes de Paris</part>
            </title>; 19th century plates depicting national dress of individuals from various social classes and professions including Italian, Swiss, and Eastern European; plates depicting 18th century French theatrical personalities in popular roles; several 19th century American dress pattern catalogs by Butterick and McCall's; and scrapbooks containing a variety of fashion, national dress, and theatrical plates dating from the 19th century.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_bf57e8b786dce0f6aa8658af47d18652">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Preliminarily arranged by type and by nationality.</p>  
      </arrangement>
